      "pagename": "history",
      "title": "Clinic History",
      "content": [
        "Dr. Donald Palmer founded the Olson Pediatric Clinic in 1972.  It was the first pediatric office in the Lake Grove area of Lake Oswego.  From the beginning, Dr. Palmer set the highest possible standard for his clinic.  He hired only Registered Nurses for his clinical staff, a policy that continues to this day.  He believed pediatric care should be both comprehensive and personal, that the care of every patient should be individualized, and that every patient should be treated like family.  He famously knew all his patients, and their parents, by name.  As his practice grew, he was careful to assure that none of these principles were compromised, eventually settling on a maximum size of five or six partners for the clinic.  This seemed to be the ideal size and structure to best serve his patients for the future.",
        "Olson Pediatric Clinic shall be forever grateful to Dr. Palmer as we continue to serve the medical needs of the children in our community."
      ],
      "imageURL": ""
    },
