            "Each well-child preventative care visit with your pediatrician will include observation and assessment of age appropriate developmental milestones. This includes screening tests at age 9, 18 and 24 months. Early identification of developmental concerns is crucial and will be addressed by subspecialty and/or early intervention referrals and subsequent care coordination by our clinic as needed. As a designated Oregon Patient-Centered Primary Care Medical Home we are committed to the high standards set by the American Academy of Pediatrics."
